parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause the wipers to stop working, reducing driver visibility, which can lead to accidents, especially during rainy or snowy conditions.
symptoms: The windshield wipers work intermittently
stop working
or activate involuntarily
and the washer fluid may spray excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into Windshield Wiper Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the windshield wiper module can cause the wipers to fail, leading to reduced driver visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water leaks into the windshield wiper module
causing the wipers to work intermittently or stop working altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper cover can allow water to enter the wiper module, leading to wiper failure and reduced driver visibility.
symptoms: The windshield wiper cover fails
allowing water to enter the wiper module
and the wipers work intermittently or stop working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PassLock system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down at random
the vehicle cannot be started
the key becomes stuck in the ignition
the lock warning indicator illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the speedometer can cause the driver to lose track of their speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer sticks at a certain speed
the speedometer fails to start at zero
the speedometer reads incorrectly
the speedometer becomes stuck at a high speed reading.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper/washer system can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers only function intermittently
the windshield washer fails to operate
the windshield wiper motor is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering knuckle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The right front wheel detaches from the vehicle
the passenger side front end drops
the vehicle slides or loses control
and the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the power steering pump shaft shears off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The tie rod breaks
causing the vehicle to lose control
and the wheel becomes difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical issues can cause the vehicle's systems to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The "check engine oil" light comes on
the engine burns oil
and there are issues with the seat memory
mirrors
and roof leaks.
